IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IChangeSetHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle
public interface IChangeSet
extends IChangeSetHandle, IAuditable

Represents a change set. A change set describes one or more changes to versionable items in a configuration. Applying those changes yield another configuration. In other words, a change set is a reified configuration delta.

A change set has a unique id (UUID) and changes (check-ins, comment changes, etc.) create new change set states. There is a current state and all other states provide an audit trail (see IAuditable for more details).

Since configurations are typically large, and change sets typically, the standard usage is to explicitly construct a change set that can be applied to a configuration. Computing a change set by diffing two configurations to not done for reasons of performance (although it would make sense in principle to do so).

Note that there are no operations on IChangeSet that modify the change set directly. A change set gets constructed and modified indirectly in the course of changing files, folders, and other versionable items in a workspace. When an aspect of the change set is modified, a new state of the change set is created. Clients are not permitted to save change sets. They are, however, allowed to retrieve a change set with fetchCurrent, fetchState, etc.

0.5
